"{\"statement\": \"Task: Given a hallway with $N+2$ tiles numbered from $0$ to $N+1$ and a hole on tile $x$, determine if a ball hit from either end of the hallway with bounces at intervals of $k$ will enter the hole either on its forward or backward journey.\\n\\nInput: The first line of input contains an integer $T$, the number of test cases. Each test case consists of a line containing three integers: $N$, $x$, and $k$. \\n\\nOutput: For each test case, output \\\"YES\\\" if the ball will enter the hole either in its forward or backward journey, and \\\"NO\\\" otherwise. The output should be in uppercase or lowercase.\\n\\nConstraints: $1 \\\\leq T \\\\leq 10^5$, $1 \\\\leq x, k \\\\leq N \\\\leq 10^9$.\", \"editorial\": \"\", \"tag\": \"['Mathematics']\", \"difficulties\": \"EASY\", \"source\": \"codechef\", \"url\": \"https://www.codechef.com/problems/LKDNGOLF\", \"sample_test_cases\": [{\"input\": \"3\\n5 4 2\\n5 3 2\\n5 5 2\", \"output\": \"YES\\nNO\\nNO\"}]}"